{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, this approach is specifically designed for ecommerce recommendations rather than dynamic news environments.",
    "Our objective is to model how users consume news over time in order to infer their preferences.",
    "Traditional ID-based methods often struggle with the coldstart problem in news recommendation due to the rapid update and short lifespan of news articles (Wu et al. 2020).",
    "To overcome these issues, neural network-based methods have been proposed to automatically learn representations of news and users (Okura et al. 2017).",
    "Sequential recommendation approaches have also gained attention, aiming to model user behaviors with deep learning-based news recommendation methods, such as RNNs, CNNs, or self-attention networks (Wu et al. 2019b; Nguyen et al. 2024; Khattar et al. 2018; Kumar et al. 2017)."
  ]
}